<p>
  One of the most tangible markers of this connection is the Jones family burial ground
  associated with lands in proximity to the estate. Burial places often preserve what other
  records do not: physical confirmation that families lived, worked, and remained rooted in a
  place across decades of change. For descendants, this burial ground stands as a quiet but
  powerful testament to the Jones family’s presence in the Biltmore world.
</p>

